===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|point|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|point|lang=fro||a point, dot, full stop, period, speck, hole, stitch, point of time, moment, difficulty, etc.}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|punctum||a point, puncture|| spot on dice, small part or weight, moment, point in space, etc.|lang=la}}, prop. a hole punched in, substantive use of {{term|punctus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|pungo|pungō|I prick, punch|lang=la}}. Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} ''[[ord#Middle English|ord]]'' "point" (from {{etyl|ang|-}} ''[[ord#Old English|ord]]'' "point").

